-- Razgulay Begins Harvesting Grain in Russia’s Krasnodar Region
-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 2012-07-11T15:57:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-11/razgulay-begins-harvesting-grain-in-russia-s-krasnodar-region.html
OAO  Razgulay Group (GRAZ)  began harvesting
grain in Russia’s Krasnodar region, the company said today in a
statement on its  website .  Razgulay plans to harvest 250,000 hectares (618,000 acres)
this year, including 81,300 hectares sown with wheat, 55,700
with  sugar beet , 27,800 with barley and 15,000 with rice.
Oilseeds are planted on more than 32,000 hectares, with 15,600
of soybeans, 9,000 of sunflowers and in excess of 8,000 of flax.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
 msysoyeva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  